    3. **Sub-pixel Accuracy**: Discard the "safe mode" for small areas. Every single white pixel in the mask, regardless of how small the underlying detail is, must be completely overwritten by the new texture.
    4. **Topology-Aware Skinning**: Wrap the new material like a physical skin over the existing geometry. It must conform to the 3D curvature of the smallest bumps and finest wrinkles without skipping.
    5. **100% Albedo Erasure**: Wipe all original color and grain. Ensure ZERO "ghosting" or remnants of the old texture in high-frequency detail areas.
